{{Infobox medical condition (new) | name = Dysgammaglobulinemia | image = | caption = | | pronounce = | field = | synonyms = | symptoms = | complications = | onset = | duration = | types = | causes = | risks = | diagnosis = | differential = | prevention = | treatment = | medication = | prognosis = | frequency = | deaths = }} '''Dysgammaglobulinemia''' is a type of [[immune disorder]] characterized by a reduction in some types of [[gamma globulin]]s, resulting in heightened susceptibility to some infectious diseases where primary immunity is antibody based.<ref>{{DorlandsDict|three/000033050|Dysgammaglobulinemia}}</ref><ref>[http://www.emedicinehealth.com/script/main/srchcont_dict.asp?src=Dysgammaglobulinemia Dysgammaglobulinemia] at [[eMedicine]] Dictionary</ref>
It is distinguished from [[hypogammaglobulinemia]], which is a reduction in ''all'' types of gamma globulins.<ref>{{DorlandsDict|four/000051615|hypogammaglobulinemia}}</ref>
[[Hyper IgM syndrome]] can be considered a form of dysgammaglobulinemia, because it results from a failure of transformation from [[IgM]] production to production of other antibodies, and so the condition can be interpreted as a reduction of the other types.
